<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{8}{y}=-{50}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{2}{y}=-{21}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({1},-{7}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --7. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{7}}{{6}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{7}}}{{6}}{\left({6}{x}+{8}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{7}}}{{6}}{\left(-{50}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{7}\right)}{x}+{9.3333333333333}{y}=-{58.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{2}{y}=-{21}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{11.333333333333}{y}=-{79.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{79.333333333333}}{{11.333333333333}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{8}{\left(-{7}\right)}=-{50}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{\left(-{56}\right)}=-{50}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{50}-{\left(-{56}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{6}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({1},-{7}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

